Histograms

Histogram * modified bar plot * cut the x-axis into equally sized chunks/intervals/“bins” ** there can be no gaps ** must cover the whole range of the data * count how many data values are in each “bin”

#uni modal data, follows a normal distribution
ggplot(mileage, aes(x = mpg)) + 
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

#bimodal
ggplot(oldfaithful, aes(x = erupt_time)) + 
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

#extremely right skewed data
ggplot(wells, aes(x = Arsenic)) +
  geom_histogram()
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

Z-score

Z-score * Z-score is a unitless magnitude that will tell us distance

\[\frac{x - \mu}{\sigma} = z-score,\] * \(\mu\) = mean * \(\sigma\) = sd * \(x-\mu\) -> distance of point from mean * \(\sigma\) -> roughly the average distance of all points + note: units will cancel each other out

Skewness and kurtosis

Skewness and kurtosis * skewness - third moment * how you quantify skewness: ** in perfectly symmetric data, the data will cancel each other out and the third moment/skewness = 0 * kurotsis can only be positive * kurtosis of a bell curve is 3 * kurtosis - fourth moment

anything that affects the mean and the standard deviation will affect the four moments

moment-based summaries in R - mean() - var() - sd() - skewness() - kurtosis(), in the moments package in r

(mean(mileage$mpg))
## [1] 36.994
(sd(mileage$mpg))
## [1] 2.417897
# on average, points are spread out about 2.42 mpg above and below the mean

library(moments)
(skewness(mileage$mpg))
## [1] 0.05014194
(kurtosis(mileage$mpg))
## [1] 3.672556

5 number summary

5-Number Summary * minimum, Q1, median, Q3, maxium * IQR = Q3 - Q1 — range of the middle 50% of the data * Range = max - min * Percentiles ** Q1 = 25th percentile/quantile ** Median = 50th percentile/quantile ** Q3 = 75th percentile/quantile

fivenum(mileage$mpg)
## [1] 30.00 35.65 37.00 38.35 44.90
fivenum(mileage$mpg)[1]
## [1] 30
range(mileage$mpg)
## [1] 30.0 44.9
diff(range(mileage$mpg))
## [1] 14.9
quantile(mileage$mpg, c(.25, .5, .75))
##    25%    50%    75% 
## 35.675 37.000 38.325
quantile(mileage$mpg, seq(.1, .9, .1)) 
##   10%   20%   30%   40%   50%   60%   70%   80%   90% 
## 33.89 35.18 36.07 36.66 37.00 37.34 37.93 38.84 40.11
#quartiles by 4 (.25, .5, .75)
#quintiles by 5 (.20, .40, .60, .80)
#deciles by 4 (.10, .20, .30, .40,..., .90)
xbar <- mean(mileage$mpg)
s <- sd(mileage$mpg)

mileage <- mileage %>% 
  mutate(zscores = (mpg - xbar)/s,
         kpl = 0.43 * mpg,
         zscoresm = (kpl - mean(mileage$kpl))/sd(mileage$kpl)
  )
